01:07:34,717 --> 01:07:36,343
Oh, I can't let you in here, sorry.

1014
01:07:36,927 --> 01:07:38,304
Stupid regulations.

1015
01:07:40,139 --> 01:07:41,348
Come on. We'll go for a walk.

1016
01:07:52,193 --> 01:07:53,194
[Sherry] So...

1017
01:07:54,153 --> 01:07:55,404
big day tomorrow, Conor.

1018
01:07:55,988 --> 01:07:57,364
The first final in how long is it?

1019
01:07:57,865 --> 01:07:58,991
Yeah, I can't do it.

1020
01:08:00,076 --> 01:08:02,495
It's just nerves. You're a great player

1021
01:08:02,703 --> 01:08:04,497
in a great team. You'll be fine.

1022
01:08:04,622 --> 01:08:06,040
That's got nothing to do with it.

1023
01:08:07,917 --> 01:08:09,585
Sir, I saw you, with your friend.

1024
01:08:09,835 --> 01:08:11,170
You were together.

1025
01:08:19,261 --> 01:08:21,180
So you saw me with
a friend, Conor. So what?

1026
01:08:25,351 --> 01:08:26,435
Look, I know it's hard,

1027
01:08:30,898 --> 01:08:31,857
I know.

1028
01:08:32,399 --> 01:08:33,317
But...

1029
01:08:34,652 --> 01:08:35,653
it gets better.

1030
01:08:36,445 --> 01:08:37,279
Trust me.

1031
01:08:37,655 --> 01:08:39,365
-When I'm older.
-Yeah, when you're older.

1032
01:08:40,032 --> 01:08:41,117
Sad fact of life.

1033
01:08:42,535 --> 01:08:43,994
So I'm just supposed to keep lying.

1034
01:08:44,078 --> 01:08:44,912
It's not a lie.

1035
01:08:45,913 --> 01:08:48,582
It's not necessarily lying if
you keep something to yourself.

1036
01:08:49,375 --> 01:08:52,169
But if you pretend to be something
you're not, then that's a lie.

1037
01:08:52,795 --> 01:08:54,839
Sir, I remember the lesson with Ned.

1038
01:08:55,005 --> 01:08:57,591
I remember when you called him
out for plagiarizing that song.

1039
01:08:58,092 --> 01:08:59,426
"Don't use a borrowed voice," you said.

1040
01:08:59,510 --> 01:09:01,178
"Find your own voice." "Don't be a sheep."

1041
01:09:01,595 --> 01:09:03,597
Sir, you said that lesson
wasn't just for Ned.

1042
01:09:03,681 --> 01:09:06,433
You said it was for all of us.
So why am I exempt?

1043
01:09:06,517 --> 01:09:08,352
Why am I different from everyone else?

1044
01:09:08,435 --> 01:09:11,522
You can't be all things to all men,
Conor, at all times.

1045
01:09:11,730 --> 01:09:13,941
-It's not smart.
-Why not?

1046
01:09:14,024 --> 01:09:16,902
Sometimes you need to keep things
hidden away. To protect yourself.

1047
01:09:24,326 --> 01:09:26,412
There will come a point in the future...

1048
01:09:27,621 --> 01:09:29,123
when you won't have to lie anymore.

1049
01:09:29,665 --> 01:09:30,666
Trust me.

1050
01:09:31,876 --> 01:09:32,877
Will there?

1051
01:09:33,627 --> 01:09:34,503
Yeah.

1052
01:09:37,006 --> 01:09:38,299
And are you at that point?

1053
01:09:38,716 --> 01:09:40,009
This isn't about me.

1054
01:09:46,015 --> 01:09:47,308
It gets better.

1055
01:09:50,185 --> 01:09:51,270
It gets better...

1056
01:09:54,690 --> 01:09:57,193
That's all I can say to you.
Please believe me, Conor.

1057
01:09:59,820 --> 01:10:01,906
How on earth can
I even begin to believe you?

1058
01:10:06,160 --> 01:10:07,453
Come on, Conor...

1059
01:10:08,287 --> 01:10:09,330
Conor...

1060
01:10:24,261 --> 01:10:26,889
[Victor] Jesus Christ, Conor - it's 11:05!

1061
01:10:31,852 --> 01:10:34,688
[Walter] We take this type
of transgression very seriously.

1062
01:10:35,522 --> 01:10:37,149
We'll take the midterm to consider.

1063
01:10:37,942 --> 01:10:39,485
But punishment will be severe.

1064
01:10:39,902 --> 01:10:41,820
I appreciate all that, thank you.

1065
01:10:42,780 --> 01:10:45,240
Tell me though, what
happened to my son's face?

1066
01:10:46,408 --> 01:10:48,202
[Walter] Well, we can't get
an answer on that, I'm afraid.

1067
01:10:49,954 --> 01:10:50,871
Ned?

1068
01:10:52,122 --> 01:10:54,333
-Nothing happened.
-Something happened...

1069
01:10:56,168 --> 01:10:58,170
This is nobody's fault but my own.

1070
01:10:59,088 --> 01:11:02,049
More than anything, this is about
preserving the ethos of the school.

1071
01:11:02,341 --> 01:11:03,676
[opening door suddenly] Sir...

1072
01:11:04,885 --> 01:11:06,804
-Sorry...
-Wait outside, Victor.

1073
01:11:09,765 --> 01:11:11,308
I can't, sir.

1074
01:11:12,268 --> 01:11:13,310
Conor's gone missing.

1075
01:11:15,938 --> 01:11:18,899
[Victor] He didn't stay
in his bed last night.

1076
01:11:19,817 --> 01:11:20,943
He's gone.

1077
01:11:21,151 --> 01:11:23,612
Well have you told Pascal--
I mean Mr. O'Keeffe?

1078
01:11:24,446 --> 01:11:26,740
No. I thought I'd come to you first.

1079
01:11:26,824 --> 01:11:29,410
Well tell Mr. O'Keeffe I want to see him
here. Immediately!

1080
01:11:29,576 --> 01:11:30,577
Go on!

1081
01:11:30,744 --> 01:11:31,704
Yes, sir.

1082
01:11:33,080 --> 01:11:33,998
[door closing behind]

1083
01:11:45,134 --> 01:11:48,470
Sir, Mr. Curly wants to see you.

1084
01:11:48,721 --> 01:11:51,640
Victor - I thought you were
supposed to be Victor and Conor.

1085
01:11:51,849 --> 01:11:52,850
Where's Conor?

1086
01:11:53,851 --> 01:11:58,314
Sir, there was an incident yesterday, and
Conor-- he's gone missing.

1087
01:11:58,647 --> 01:12:00,065
Okay - what do you mean "missing," Victor?

1088
01:12:00,232 --> 01:12:02,276
Walter wants to see you, sir. Now.

1089
01:12:02,609 --> 01:12:04,862
Walter wants to see me...

1090
01:12:06,488 --> 01:12:08,115
[whispering] Of course this
has to happen today.

1091
01:12:09,324 --> 01:12:10,326
Thank you, Victor.

1092
01:12:19,710 --> 01:12:21,545
Hey, Pascal. Good luck today.

1093
01:12:22,254 --> 01:12:23,505
Are you okay?

1094
01:12:25,549 --> 01:12:27,217
You're delighted, Sherry, huh?

1095
01:12:28,344 --> 01:12:29,678
Over the fucken moon, yeah!

1096
01:12:31,346 --> 01:12:33,223
-Uh... what?
-Conor Masters, huh?

1097
01:12:33,891 --> 01:12:35,392
Missing - on the day of the final...

1098
01:12:36,560 --> 01:12:38,520
-Missing?
-Missing! Yes!

1099
01:12:38,729 --> 01:12:40,355
What part of "missing"
don't you understand?

1100
01:12:53,494 --> 01:12:54,411
[knocking on door]

1101
01:13:25,109 --> 01:13:26,276
When we get back...

1102
01:13:26,610 --> 01:13:28,445
can I please jump out in town?

1103
01:13:28,695 --> 01:13:30,364
I really need to do something.

1104
01:13:31,115 --> 01:13:32,533
You must be kidding...

1105
01:13:38,997 --> 01:13:42,084
Look, Dad, I know I'm in trouble,

1106
01:13:42,209 --> 01:13:44,253
but I wouldn't ask if it
wasn't absolutely vital.

1107
01:13:45,045 --> 01:13:47,881
Not only are you not "jumping out," Ned,

1108
01:13:48,090 --> 01:13:51,051
you are massively, unbelievably grounded

1109
01:13:51,135 --> 01:13:53,011
until we can figure out
what to do with you.

1110
01:14:01,812 --> 01:14:03,021
Tanner, feet down.

1111
01:14:05,983 --> 01:14:06,984
Dan.

1112
01:14:12,489 --> 01:14:14,366
I suppose you've
heard about Conor Masters.

1113
01:14:14,700 --> 01:14:15,617
Yeah.

1114
01:14:17,035 --> 01:14:18,620
His parents don't know where he is.

1115
01:14:19,621 --> 01:14:21,498
Well, I've notified
the guards anyway, so...

1116
01:14:25,169 --> 01:14:27,713
And we have an untested player at outhalf.

1117
01:14:30,007 --> 01:14:31,717
And Wallace is - at best--

1118
01:14:31,800 --> 01:14:33,844
Oh who cares about
the fucking rugby, Walter?

1119
01:14:36,263 --> 01:14:37,681
Some boys don't play rugby.

1120
01:14:40,058 --> 01:14:41,185
What about those boys?

1121
01:15:17,846 --> 01:15:20,432
Ned! Ned!

1122
01:15:20,515 --> 01:15:21,767
Fuck...

1123
01:15:31,318 --> 01:15:33,487
[Ned] Conor was always running.

1124
01:15:34,154 --> 01:15:37,991
I couldn't understand it, 
but now I finally got it.

1125
01:15:38,242 --> 01:15:41,078
You have to know that you're 
running in the right direction.

1126
01:16:09,648 --> 01:16:10,649
Men.

1127
01:16:14,027 --> 01:16:16,154
You might be wondering
where our outhalf is.

1128
01:16:19,825 --> 01:16:23,120
Earlier, as you know, I was called to Mr.
Curly's office

1129
01:16:23,245 --> 01:16:25,080
and informed that the boy has...

1130
01:16:26,081 --> 01:16:27,666
had some kind of breakdown,

1131
01:16:28,542 --> 01:16:29,751
and has gone missing.

1132
01:16:31,211 --> 01:16:32,462
Today of all days, I know...

1133
01:16:35,048 --> 01:16:37,718
I don't know if you were aware of the
rumors swirling around,

1134
01:16:39,219 --> 01:16:41,555
but it transpires that
he was dealing with...

1135
01:16:43,140 --> 01:16:44,474
serious personal issues.

1136
01:16:45,017 --> 01:16:47,686
Well he's missing today,
and I want to tell you this:

1137
01:16:50,564 --> 01:16:53,066
we are way better off without him.

1138
01:16:54,359 --> 01:16:56,695
I mean, we all have personal issues,

1139
01:16:57,904 --> 01:16:59,156
but look around you!

1140
01:17:00,032 --> 01:17:01,575
Anyone who can't be trusted

1141
01:17:01,992 --> 01:17:05,412
to put those issues to one
side can't be part of a team.

1142
01:17:06,538 --> 01:17:07,539
Yeah...

1143
01:17:10,917 --> 01:17:13,003
We all have shit that we're
going through, you know.

1144
01:17:15,714 --> 01:17:16,673
But do you run?

1145
01:17:19,509 --> 01:17:20,385
No.

1146
01:17:23,305 --> 01:17:24,348
You stay.

1147
01:17:26,475 --> 01:17:28,602
You stay, and deal with your shit,

1148
01:17:28,977 --> 01:17:30,437
by standing in a field

1149
01:17:31,188 --> 01:17:33,649
blowing a whistle in the fucking rain!

1150
01:17:39,821 --> 01:17:42,449
[indistinct cheering]

1151
01:18:59,568 --> 01:19:00,485
Hello?

1152
01:19:10,704 --> 01:19:11,788
Can I come in?

1153
01:19:12,956 --> 01:19:13,957
What do you want?

1154
01:19:17,002 --> 01:19:18,003
I want to apologize...

1155
01:19:19,212 --> 01:19:20,505
for being a terrible friend.

1156
01:19:23,258 --> 01:19:24,718
So you knew about me all along.

1157
01:19:26,803 --> 01:19:28,096
I'm so sorry, Conor...

1158
01:19:34,478 --> 01:19:35,645
I want you to play.

1159
01:19:36,188 --> 01:19:37,189
There's still time.

1160
01:19:37,689 --> 01:19:39,149
You said that that wasn't your team.

1161
01:19:39,649 --> 01:19:41,526
You've never even seen us play before.

1162
01:19:42,277 --> 01:19:43,570
Yeah look - I was wrong.

1163
01:19:44,946 --> 01:19:48,074
Okay? Turns out I was wrong
about pretty much everything.

1164
01:19:51,161 --> 01:19:52,204
Not everything...

1165
01:19:57,250 --> 01:19:59,878
You don't have to pick a side, Conor.

1166
01:20:00,295 --> 01:20:02,964
You don't have to be one thing or the
other. You can be everything.

1167
01:20:04,925 --> 01:20:06,676
I'm not sure I can play for them.

1168
01:20:06,968 --> 01:20:08,386
For Weasel.

1169
01:20:09,471 --> 01:20:11,515
-For the Coach.
-It's not for them!

1170
01:20:12,432 --> 01:20:15,477
You're not playing for them.
You're playing for us.

1171
01:20:16,144 --> 01:20:18,522
It's my team if you're playing for it.

1172
01:20:20,106 --> 01:20:21,650
Reveal to them who you are.

1173
01:20:23,235 --> 01:20:24,402
If you dare...

1174
01:20:27,447 --> 01:20:28,782
If you dare...

1175
01:20:35,455 --> 01:20:36,623
Our team yeah.

1176
01:21:00,188 --> 01:21:01,565
[referee blowing the whistle]

1177
01:22:02,375 --> 01:22:03,335
Conor.

1178
01:22:06,171 --> 01:22:07,255
What can we do for you?

1179
01:22:08,256 --> 01:22:10,634
Late again. Sorry about that, lads...

1180
01:22:11,718 --> 01:22:14,304
Your mind is shot, right?

1181
01:22:15,555 --> 01:22:17,474
You're all over the place.
I understand that.

1182
01:22:19,351 --> 01:22:20,894
How is it shot?

1183
01:22:21,770 --> 01:22:23,313
Well... at this point...

1184
01:22:24,397 --> 01:22:26,441
we all heard about the thing...

1185
01:22:28,151 --> 01:22:29,110
The thing?

1186
01:22:30,195 --> 01:22:31,154
The thing...

1187
01:22:31,738 --> 01:22:33,698
-The thing?
-The thing! The thing! The thing!

1188
01:22:34,949 --> 01:22:35,784
Lookit,

1189
01:22:36,326 --> 01:22:37,494
it's not your fault,

1190
01:22:38,495 --> 01:22:40,246
but you cannot fit into this team.

1191
01:22:40,413 --> 01:22:43,166
-Since when?
-Since-- lookit, you're incompatible.

1192
01:22:43,583 --> 01:22:45,043
Incompatible according to who?

1193
01:22:45,251 --> 01:22:46,252
Us.

1194
01:22:47,921 --> 01:22:49,547
According to all of us.
Isn't that right, lads?

1195
01:22:55,762 --> 01:22:57,597
I don't know if you heard
why I left my old school...

1196
01:22:59,432 --> 01:23:03,019
Yeah. We heard you got in some fights.

1197
01:23:05,689 --> 01:23:07,273
...and I don't know if you
heard why I was fighting.

1198
01:23:11,695 --> 01:23:13,947
I was fighting everyone
who found out who I was.

1199
01:23:15,281 --> 01:23:17,659
Every last one of them. But...

1200
01:23:19,035 --> 01:23:20,328
they kept coming.

1201
01:23:21,830 --> 01:23:24,874
I couldn't stop them coming,
and I couldn't fight them all.

1202
01:23:27,127 --> 01:23:29,754
I couldn't stay and keep
denying it so I ran away,

1203
01:23:30,755 --> 01:23:31,881
to our school...

1204
01:23:33,883 --> 01:23:35,010
Thing is, lads...

1205
01:23:37,679 --> 01:23:39,139
I'd like to stop running away, you know.

1206
01:23:40,223 --> 01:23:41,099
I'm done with that.

1207
01:23:43,435 --> 01:23:44,686
Thanks to Ned here...

1208
01:23:45,353 --> 01:23:46,354
you all know who I am.

1209
01:23:47,188 --> 01:23:49,858
I'm the same me I always
was and I really really

1210
01:23:50,316 --> 01:23:51,860
really want to be a part of this team.

1211
01:23:54,779 --> 01:23:57,657
I'm here, and I'm ready to play. So...

1212
01:23:58,074 --> 01:23:59,784
if you want me on your side, just...

1213
01:24:05,582 --> 01:24:07,125
Wallace has been

1214
01:24:08,168 --> 01:24:10,420
filling in at ten and
doing a perfectly good job.

1215
01:24:10,795 --> 01:24:13,006
-C'mon Pascal...
-No I haven't, Pascal.

1216
01:24:13,173 --> 01:24:14,382
Believe in yourself, boy.

1217
01:24:15,383 --> 01:24:17,802
I believe I'm fucking shit at out-half.

1218
01:24:19,429 --> 01:24:20,555
I'm a winger and you know it.

1219
01:24:26,478 --> 01:24:28,688
Come on, Pascal.
Just put Wallace on the wing.

1220
01:24:28,897 --> 01:24:32,317
Well that's a pity, Victor, 'cos Wallace
has just put himself on the bench!

1221
01:24:33,109 --> 01:24:35,278
There is one coach on this team.

1222
01:24:35,695 --> 01:24:37,697
One voice. Not fifteen!

1223
01:24:38,114 --> 01:24:39,199
You hear me?

1224
01:24:42,077 --> 01:24:43,369
Do you hear me, Victor?

1225
01:24:52,629 --> 01:24:54,631
Congratulations Victor,
you're off the team and all!

1226
01:25:03,014 --> 01:25:06,559
Tom Quinlan, Keith Shafrey, you're both
subbed off, you pair of eejits.

1227
01:25:10,605 --> 01:25:12,023
You pair of fucking tools.

1228
01:25:12,273 --> 01:25:15,443
Lads, I'm sorry, but this lot have
ruined your hard work for the year.

1229
01:25:22,117 --> 01:25:24,828
Anyone else walks over to that
side and they're gone too.

1230
01:25:31,417 --> 01:25:34,379
I'll forfeit the game if I have to!

1231
01:25:35,255 --> 01:25:36,798
I can do that!

1232
01:25:38,716 --> 01:25:41,636
That's enough I said! You hear me?

1233
01:25:57,318 --> 01:25:59,028
Ah, for fuck's sake.

1234
01:26:24,470 --> 01:26:26,514
We all have that one
thing we're ashamed of.

1235
01:26:28,016 --> 01:26:30,185
A memory of one moment so embarrassing

1236
01:26:30,602 --> 01:26:32,562
we don't know if we'll
ever be able to forget it.

1237
01:26:34,814 --> 01:26:38,443
Single moments when, not only do we
betray everyone around us,

1238
01:26:38,902 --> 01:26:42,113
but we betray ourselves too
in the most terrible way.

1239
01:26:46,576 --> 01:26:48,578
[Ned continues] Yes, 
we all have that moment.

1240
01:26:49,245 --> 01:26:52,415
But the pain of remembering the
embarrassment begins to fade eventually,

1241
01:26:53,166 --> 01:26:55,168
with the help of a good friend.

1242
01:26:58,546 --> 01:27:01,758
I will never forget that 
game for as long as I live.

1243
01:27:02,383 --> 01:27:05,595
Conor was everywhere. Everyone noticed it.

1244
01:27:05,845 --> 01:27:08,097
The determination to shut people up.

1245
01:27:08,306 --> 01:27:09,599
To prove them wrong.

1246
01:27:09,849 --> 01:27:12,727
What he was feeling spread 
throughout the team like a fever.

1247
01:27:12,936 --> 01:27:15,605
People talked about it 
for months afterwards.

1248
01:28:01,025 --> 01:28:03,611
-Conor's playing!
-Yeah. Young Ned found him.

1249
01:28:07,490 --> 01:28:09,742
Well he's a good kid. Ned.

1250
01:28:16,124 --> 01:28:18,042
Walter, this is Arthur.

1251
01:28:19,127 --> 01:28:21,170
Hello, Arthur. Walter.

1252
01:28:23,506 --> 01:28:25,174
Arthur's me fella.

1253
01:28:28,553 --> 01:28:30,096
We're a bit of "an item."

1254
01:28:51,659 --> 01:28:53,036
[Ned] Like I said...

1255
01:28:53,369 --> 01:28:56,122
I don't think I'll ever be able
to get over the embarrassment

1256
01:28:56,247 --> 01:28:57,790
and the shame of what I did.

1257
01:28:58,583 --> 01:29:01,419
But in a way, some good
did come out of it...

1258
01:29:04,255 --> 01:29:07,842
That year, everyone in school
learned the same lesson.

1259
01:29:08,384 --> 01:29:10,845
Not to speak in a borrowed voice.

1260
01:29:40,708 --> 01:29:42,460
[yelling indistinctly]

1261
01:29:50,384 --> 01:29:51,636
[yelling indistinctly]

1262
01:30:36,055 --> 01:30:38,850
You know, one single year before...

1263
